			"type": "text",
			"text": "Priapulites konecniorum comes from the upper Carboniferous, with fossils found in the Francis Creek Shale, USA. It is a elongated priapulid, and grew up to 6 cm in length. It is currently accepted to be the oldest known crown-group Priapulid worm. The specific name derives from the surname of Mr. and Mrs. James Konecny, who donated the first fossil material."
